{
  "stem": "12462.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Who was he?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was Gustav Krupp von Bohlen und Halbach.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the head of the huge Krupp concern, which was the greatest armament concern of all Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had been the head of a group, called the Hitler Circle of Friends, that had made vast contributions over the years to the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was, later on, another similar thing called, the Himmler Circle of Friends, but that's not the same thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The judgments were made on October 1, 1946.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the judgment was read during the first day, one whole day and the beginning of the morning on the-- well, most of the morning on the second day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the sentences were not pronounced, until after the judges and everybody else had had lunch, including the defendants.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think, 11 of the 20 that were tried were convicted of conspiracy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many more of them were convicted of spoliation of property of foreign countries, or slave labor, or responsibility for the concentration camps, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I-- I couldn't tell you by numbers exactly how many.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Three were found not guilty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the total number found guilty was 19.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they were not found guilty on all counts, as I've indicated earlier.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "For instance, Schirach was not found guilty on count one, but was found guilty on count four.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were several cases like that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Franz von Papen, who had been the chancellor of Germany just before Hitler and who had helped arrange to put Hitler in power, as a part of a deal that was worked out at that time-- he was one.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
